spec: asyncio_extra110
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(asyncio)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio-sync.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio-sync.html — Python asyncio synchronization primitives documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/asyncio/locks.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec extends asyncio_extra109.zspec.zsdl."
    - "This spec covers: wave 254 theme — asyncio.Lock, asyncio.Semaphore, asyncio.BoundedSemaphore, asyncio.Event method code attributes: acquire/release co_argcount values. NEW in extra110: asyncio.Lock.acquire.__qualname__=='Lock.acquire' (len=12, co_argcount=1: self only); asyncio.Lock.release.__qualname__=='Lock.release' (len=12, co_argcount=1: self only); asyncio.Semaphore.acquire.__qualname__=='Semaphore.acquire' (len=17, co_argcount=1: self only); asyncio.Semaphore.release.__qualname__=='Semaphore.release' (len=17, co_argcount=1: self only); asyncio.BoundedSemaphore.release.__qualname__=='BoundedSemaphore.release' (len=24, longest qualname in spec, co_argcount=1); asyncio.Event.set.__qualname__=='Event.set' (len=9, shortest in spec, co_argcount=1); asyncio.Event.clear.__qualname__=='Event.clear' (len=11, co_argcount=1); asyncio.Event.wait.__qualname__=='Event.wait' (len=10, co_argcount=1); asyncio.Lock.__module__=='asyncio.locks'; asyncio.Lock.__bases__[0].__name__=='_ContextManagerMixin', __mro__.__len__()==4; asyncio.Semaphore.__bases__[0].__name__=='_ContextManagerMixin', __mro__.__len__()==4; asyncio.BoundedSemaphore.__bases__[0].__name__=='Semaphore', __mro__.__len__()==5; asyncio.Event.__bases__[0].__name__=='_LoopBoundMixin', __mro__.__len__()==3. All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.Lock.acquire.__qualname__ == 'Lock.acquire' (len=12). type is function (Python-defined coroutine). co_argcount=1 (self only — all async acquire/release methods take only self). Lock.__module__=='asyncio.locks'; Lock.__bases__[0].__name__=='_ContextManagerMixin' (MRO=[Lock, _ContextManagerMixin, object, ...], length=4). Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.BoundedSemaphore.release.__qualname__ == 'BoundedSemaphore.release' (len=24, longest qualname in spec). BoundedSemaphore.__bases__[0].__name__=='Semaphore' (inherits from Semaphore, MRO length=5, longest in spec). BoundedSemaphore.acquire.__qualname__=='Semaphore.acquire' (len=17 — inherited from Semaphore, not overridden). Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.Event.set, clear, wait all have co_argcount=1 (self only). Event.set.__qualname__=='Event.set' (len=9, shortest in spec); Event.clear.__qualname__=='Event.clear' (len=11); Event.wait.__qualname__=='Event.wait' (len=10). Event.__bases__[0].__name__=='_LoopBoundMixin' (MRO length=3). Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

